(-w is use to remove the write permission we are unable to sentensce chmod -w demo click enter ls -al its show you r-r-r-- only read (we have to change it command chmod +w demo
enter ls -al its shows you demo  in rw - rw- r now its read and write and ./hello.sh and  file name demo enter its show to write sentence  hai how are you to check it we have to
use the cat > demo its you what you enter in demo file and to execute chmod +x to execute command 

